<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
These two new species are found along waterways and under mud and stones amidst many different plants and shrubs (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 14. Landscape of habitat in Wuxiangguangchang (A, B) and in Wujiazhai (C, D) in Xishuangbanna, Yunnan, China." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.947.51067.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/430212" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">14</figureCitation>
). They seem to be living near humid sand with water nearby. The adults were collected during the month of August. They can jump from both the ground and water.
</paragraph>
